manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: LEGO City Great Vehicles - ATV Race Team This set offers an age-appropriate build and play experience for ages 5-12. Accessory elements include a wrench, fuel barrel and a spare tire. Gear up for the big race! Get ready to race with the LEGO City ATV Race Team. This set features two ATVs, a pickup truck, trailer hitch, pickup bed with adjustable ramp and a detachable trailer with adjustable ramp, plus helmets, fuel barrel and a spare tire. Includes two minifigures. Pickup truck measures over 2” (7cm) high, 5” (15cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide. Trailer measures over 1” (3cm) high, 5” (14cm) long and 2” (6cm) wide. ATVs each measure over 1” (3cm) high, 1” (5cm) long and 1” (4cm) wide.

Explore the many features & functionalities Features a pickup truck, trailer and two ATVs. Trailer features space up front for an extra wheel and ramp. Pickup truck features a pickup bed with room for an ATV, trailer hitch and a ramp.
Use the wrench and fuel barrel to prep the ATVs. Load up the ATVs on the truck and trailer. Detach the trailer from the pickup truck and unload the ATVs. Includes two ATV rider minifigures.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A definite must have for any LEGO collection.
reviews.reviewText: A fun little LEGO set with lots of playability. With a very large piece to price ratio, you can't go wrong with this set. Add some enjoyment to your bricker's day by purchasing this set.The truck that comes with this set is actually quite large and very durable... so for those rough brickers out there (like my 3 year old son), this truck should hold up just fine. The truck is also large enough to hold a small ATV vehicle in the bed. The truck has two ramps that go up and down to assist in the loading process of the ATV.The trailer hooks up to the truck and can haul the other ATV that comes with the set. The trailer as well has two ramps to help with loading and unloading the ATVs.The two minifigs that come with this set are pretty standard, however, they do the trick.All in all, I would recommend this set. Though the set retails at $19.99, I would suggest waiting to find it for at least 20% off. If you're lucky, you might even find it for 30-40% off which makes this set a 'definite' buy.Great set with lots of playability.If my review was helpful, please click on 'helpful' below. If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.Happy bricking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2017
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great addition to any Lego collection, great for hours of fun!!
reviews.reviewText: We have become Lego freaks as of late, the grandkids are really getting into building and creating their own projects, This set was so much fun to put together as a family, I have the kids find each piece as it's needed, and use the instruction book to help put it in the correct place. Even at ages 5 & 7 they are able to follow the directions, which are detailed, easy to follow, pictures. We started by building the ATV's first and of course the minifigs, (we lost the 5 yr old here, because the ATVs were just too much fun ). Then we built the truck and trailer. Once assembled it is a very sturdy piece, the kids drive the truck and trailer all around as well as the ATVs, and we have t lost any pieces.we have a lot of new sets and this is by far their favorite. I think we may need to purchase a second set !! Highly recommend.. fun for the whole family

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Lego Kit for Kids Age 4-7
reviews.reviewText: This Lego set was a gift for my 6 year old grandson. Of the gifts we gave him for Christmas, this was the one he wanted to play with first. He and I, along with his 4 year old sister, enjoyed putting it together. All of the pieces were there and the instructions were spot on. The set does have some really small parts, but if the pieces are grouped by type it was easy for him to put together and he barely looked at the directions. Great price through Amazon. Definitely recommend for lasting play-ability as the vehicles are really sturdy once put together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of playability!
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for my 6yr old nephew. His dad's into trucks, and my nephew's always been into matchbox cars, and racing toys. This Lego set was just right for him, and gave him and his dad a project they could do together. He did need minimal help, but was so excited and proud of himself afterwards. This has a lot of playability. It is a decent sized box, and is great for gifting on it's own. I definitely recommend this!

reviews.reviewText: Bought this set because I had to sell my truck, so this made me feel better about having to give the old rust bucket up. I love the ramps on both the truck and the trailer. I haven't had a set like this in a number of years, and was happy to see they improved the trailer connection. it feels more like a real trailer would at this scale. Took me about an hour to put it all together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this Lego Set
reviews.reviewText: I originally bought this lego set for my 4 year old son not knowing if it would be too difficult or not. It was the perfect skill level for him to do by himself with little help! He plays with this for hours after he built it. He loves it. His friend just had a birthday and we purchased it for him as well. Great value for your money.
Es tal y cómo se describe el producto

Our two boys are now at the age where they can build these Lego sets on their own, and they love them. Keeps them occupied in building the set, and they will then play with and adapt the sets as they go along. Storage of completed sets to avoid damage I guess would be the only 'con', but its a minor one on the grand scheme of things.Lego is one of those rare toys I don't mind buying - our kids always come back to their Lego sets, and will sit building new things for hours at a time from their imaginations. Much rather buy toys like this than the usual plastic tut that gets an hour of attention, and then just takes up space in the house for years without ever being played with again.This set was easy enough to build, our eight year old did it all himself with no help needed from dad any more. Just wish these sets were a bit cheaper - Lego seems to have gotten so expensive over the years!

It was a competitive price for the product which made it an easy choice to order. Can’t go wrong w LEGO if it’s an age appropriate set. ;-) was delivered when said to be, and in time for a Birthday, making somebody very happy.
